What an unusual error message. To net out the important part, it is:

java.lang.ClassFormatError: 
com/ibm/sse/editor/internal/search/FindOccurrencesActionProvider (Illegal UTF8 
string in constant pool)

According to the "data" here in the report, this is on Sun's 1.4.2_05, on 
Window's XP. Same system I (sometimes) use, and don't see this error. Did you, 
by chance, recompile the code using Eclipse 3.1 stream? (with a 1.5 JRE?). If 
not that, I wonder if could be related to your locale (or, more specifically, 
your default encoding). Other than that, I'd guess a corrupted zip file, or 
similar, and would suggest tring a "new" install?

I've checked several builds, including original contribution, and most recently
the I20041202 I-build and can not reproduce this problem. Plus, the error messages
posted seem rather "odd" and may indicate a bad download, or something. Please
re-open with more details if you see again.
verifying classified correctly and not a problem.
